From: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 03:10:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 28/30] dt-bindings: soc: mediatek: add MT6797 display
 mutex

MT6797 has the original MediaTek display mutex register layout, but unlike
MT6795 and MT8173 it has no dedicated mutex clock gate. Add its compatible
without adding it to the conditional clock requirement.

Signed-off-by: Gemini PDA Mainline Project <noreply@example.com>
---
 .../bindings/soc/mediatek/mediatek,mutex.yaml                 | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/mediatek/mediatek,mutex.yaml b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/mediatek/mediatek,mutex.yaml
--- a/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/mediatek/mediatek,mutex.yaml
+++ b/Documentation/devicetree/bindings/soc/mediatek/mediatek,mutex.yaml
@@ -33,6 +33,7 @@ properties:
       - mediatek,mt2701-disp-mutex
       - mediatek,mt2712-disp-mutex
       - mediatek,mt6795-disp-mutex
+      - mediatek,mt6797-disp-mutex
       - mediatek,mt8167-disp-mutex
       - mediatek,mt8173-disp-mutex
       - mediatek,mt8183-disp-mutex
-- 
